'''Trihexalon''', also called '''dragon's breath'''<ref name="JSF5c">''[[Star Wars: Jedi Starfighter]]'': "dragon's breath" cinematic</ref> and '''hex''' for short, was a chemical weapon of mass destruction. The [[Trade Federation/Legends|Trade Federation's]] dragon's breath was formed from [[Ore/Legends|ore]] mined at [[Mount Merakan]] on [[Maramere]],<ref name="JSF7">''[[Star Wars: Jedi Starfighter]]'' Mission 7: "Mount Merakan"</ref> and refined and weaponized at a factory on [[Nod Kartha]].<ref name="JSF8">''[[Star Wars: Jedi Starfighter]]'' Mission 8: "Hammer and Anvil"</ref>

==Characteristics==
Trihexalon was infamous in the [[Karthakk system]] as a deadly and highly dangerous weapon&mdash;so much so that the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] banned it because of its deadly potential.<ref name="JSF6">''[[Star Wars: Jedi Starfighter]]'' Mission 6: "Poisoned Skies"</ref> It was known to cause "complete biomass conversion" in victims,<ref name="JSF8" /> and could be refined to target individual beings<ref name="JSF5c" /> or for use as a planetary bombardment weapon.<ref name="JSF6" /> In refined form, trihexalon was a dust-like substance that gave off a toxic, green glow, and became inert and stable at very low temperatures, a major reason for the factory being on [[Nod Kartha]].

Small doses like the sample produced for [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Cavik Toth]] could be held in special vials, and would react upon release, causing an energy burst capable of instantly killing [[Humanoid/Legends|Humanoids]]. A single, palm-sized vial contained enough dragon's breath to kill three hundred [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiees]], though simply shattering the vial would only generate a blast of a few meters in size. The aftermath of a hex blast was implied to be horrific and gruesome; Toth immediately ordered droids to clean up the remains of [[Harro Ruuk]] and his subordinates after killing them with a sample vial they had just given him.<ref name="JSF5c" />

==History==
Captain Cavik Toth of [[Sabaoth Squadron/Legends|Sabaoth Squadron]] first tested it by launching [[Hex missile|missiles]] and sending [[Hex Bomber|bombers]] to destroy [[Point Modie]] on Maramere, which would have killed approximately one thousand civilians had [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Adi Gallia/Legends|Adi Gallia]] not intervened and destroyed the missiles launched before impact, with the help of the [[Lok Revenants/Legends|Lok Revenants]]. She decided the threat should be eliminated, teaming up with the space [[Pirate/Legends|pirate]] [[Nym/Legends|Nym]] and his crew.<ref name="JSF6" /> They broke through the orbital defenses at Nod Kartha, the planet churning out hex weapons.<ref name="JSF8" /> With precision flying and teamwork, they stopped the further production of such weapons.<ref name="JSF10">''[[Star Wars: Jedi Starfighter]]'' Mission 10: "Dragon's Den"</ref>

During the [[First Battle of Geonosis/Legends|Battle of Geonosis]], Toth brought a fleet of [[Hex Deployer]]s and Bombers to help the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]] triumph over the Republic. Jedi Master Adi Gallia, her Padawan, [[Siri Tachi/Legends|Siri Tachi]], Nym, and his Revenants plus a squadron of other Jedi, foiled Toth's ambitions by destroying his fleet of hex weapons. Toth was killed in the battle.<ref name="JSF15">''[[Star Wars: Jedi Starfighter]]'' Mission 15: "The Jedi Master"</ref>

During the [[Battle of Skye]], genetics terrorist [[Zeta Magnus]] threatened the planet with total destruction by unleashing a [[trihexalon-based rooze]], but was foiled in his plot by the efforts of [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]], [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]], and [[Halagad Ventor]].<ref name="SkyeWalkers: A Clone Wars Story">''[[SkyeWalkers: A Clone Wars Story]]''</ref>

Sometime during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], a group of [[Padawan/Legends|Padawans]] led by [[Mavra Zane]] and [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]] discovered a plot headed by [[Count/Legends|Count]] [[Dooku/Legends|Dooku]] and [[Shu Mai/Legends|Shu Mai]] of the [[Commerce Guild/Legends|Commerce Guild]] to spread the deadly gas on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] through the use of a [[Subjugator-class heavy cruiser/Legends|''Subjugator''-class heavy cruiser]] that was modified for the distribution of the trihexalon. However, the plot was [[Trihexalon attack on Coruscant|thwarted]] when Zane and Chewbacca, flying in the ''[[Star Runner]]'', led the aforementioned group of Padawans into the [[Subjugator (Subjugator-class)|''Subjugator'']] and destroyed the main reactor, subsequently destroying the battleship.<ref name="KSW">''[[Kinect Star Wars]]''</ref>

In [[41 ABY]], [[Jaden Korr]] was led to a [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn]]-era [[Imperial research facility]] by a [[Force vision/Legends|Force vision]]. There he found records requesting that the experiments in the facility be terminated by trihexalon gas protocol, indicating that knowledge of the gas either survived the Clone Wars, or a similar poison was later discovered by Imperial [[Scientist/Legends|scientists]].<ref name="Crosscurrent">''[[Crosscurrent]]''</ref>

